umwezi.','Accept me as tourist if you don\'t want me as President - Lungu','','publish','open','open','','accept-me-as-tourist-if-you-dont-want-me-as-president-lungu','','','2017-02-22 09:46:34','2017-02-22 09:46:34','',0,'https://staging.themastonline.com/?p=12',0,'post','',0),(13,1,'2017-02-22 09:45:48','2017-02-22 09:45:48','','16836259_1861537390770976_7189101925225059163_o','','inherit','open','closed','','16836259_1861537390770976_7189101925225059163_o','','','2017-02-22 09:45:48','2017-02-22 09:45:48','',12,'https://staging.themastonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/16836259_1861537390770976_7189101925225059163_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(14,1,'2017-02-22 09:45:50','2017-02-22 09:45:50','IF you don\'t accept me as President of Zambia, accept me as a tourist, Edgar Lungu has told Livingstone residents.\r\n\r\nSpeaking on arrival at Harry Mwaanga Nkumbula International Airport yesterday, President Lungu said he was free to go wherever he wanted in Zambia.\r\n\r\n\"One Zambia, One Nation. I know some of you are asking: what is the President doing in Livingstone? Livingstone is a tourist capital and if you don\'t accept me as President of Zambia, accept me as a tourist. I know you think that this is a joke but there are some people who believe that I am not President,\" President Lungu said.\r\n\r\nHe said that those that thought he was not the Head of State were living in their own world.\r\n\r\nPresident Lungu said he would not recognise those saying he lost the August 11, 2016 presidential elections.\r\n\r\n\"I will not force you if you don\'t want to work with me...I am a Nsenga speaking person. We are told that if your mother marries a man, that man becomes your father whether you like it or not. If you don\'t want to respect the man, they will keep you out of the village and you will suffer alone. Those who are playing games by saying I am not President, the consequences may be too bad for them because I will not recognise them. Don\'t complain